Install Brave, Chrome Browsers

Install xCode from AppStore. beware its of 12GB. You can try installing CLT xcode-select --install, developer.apple.com/downloads or Xcode 3 as mentioned in Brew Installation Page
xcode-select â€”-install works

Install Brew - /bin/bash -c "$(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Homebrew/install/HEAD/install.sh)". Source - https://brew.sh/

Install iTerm
brew install iterm2

Download Font for iterm2
git clone https://github.com/powerline/fonts.git
cd fonts
./install.sh

Change to Font - navigate to iTerm2 > Preferences > Profiles > Text > Change Font
Inconsolata for powerline
screenshot - https://cdn-media-1.freecodecamp.org/images/flJ1CL1uDv0QoX-TK0MBgn7CVuyG0wOG388V

Install Color Theme in iTerm2
iTerm2 > Preferences > Profile > Colors > Color Presets > Import
source - https://github.com/Navdit/macOS/blob/master/iTerm2_Colors_Config.itermcolors

brew install micro

brew install zsh

zsh theme
git clone --depth=1 https://github.com/romkatv/powerlevel10k.git ${ZSH_CUSTOM:-$HOME/.oh-my-zsh/custom}/themes/powerlevel10k

zsh plugins
docker
git clone https://github.com/zsh-users/zsh-docker.git ${ZSH_CUSTOM:-~/.oh-my-zsh/custom}/plugins/zsh-docker

zsh-syntax-highlighting
git clone https://github.com/zsh-users/zsh-syntax-highlighting.git ${ZSH_CUSTOM:-~/.oh-my-zsh/custom}/plugins/zsh-syntax-highlighting

zsh auto-suggestions
git clone https://github.com/zsh-users/zsh-autosuggestions ${ZSH_CUSTOM:-~/.oh-my-zsh/custom}/plugins/zsh-autosuggestions

copy zsh config file - https://github.com/Navdit/macOS/blob/master/.zsrh_config
micro ~/.zshrc



